dering whether a subclass can define its own `readResolve`. If the generated object class includes a private `readResolve`, it complicates things, especially for modules that extend `Serializable`. In that case, the call to `Enumeration.readResolve` might not be reached. I should think about whether I can test or inspect this behavior; however, I can’t run tests according to instructions, so I’ll need to reason through this to understand how it functions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_L1E5InKeDYUYltWIpvtnOpMB|fc_0b38708c41f3afbd016a1047e5b1b88191ba758b8d58cd7e12", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2796, "output": 1040, "cacheRead": 9728, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 13564, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779451861200, "responseId": "resp_0b38708c41f3afbd016a1047d58c548191920346c98f2456e4"}}
